        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Corneal dystrophy-perceptive deafness (CDPD) or Harboyan syndrome is a degenerative corneal disorder characterized by the association of congenital hereditary endothelial dystrophy (CHED) with progressive postlingual sensorineural hearing loss."
